me or beginning to roll out a proven food concept, its no longer just about location, taste, presentation, recruitment, marketing and design after all.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Like so many of you, Ive worked with good and bad food businesses since washing up and preparing pub lunches at the age of 14. The subjects of food, customers, profit, chefs and success have fascinated and frustrated me so much that Ive made them my life, committing to being scientific and structured in reviewing and proposing safe, sensible but profitable solutions for fellow business owners. Why? Because over the last few years Ive seen enough to convince me that truly successful, profitable, food led businesses are more than just a chance balance of art and science. Theyre rare and almost incredible  and I love them.</p>\r\n<p><img src="{CCM:FID_93}" alt="IMG_0139small.jpg" width="177" height="200" /></p>'),
