(820, '<h3 class="MsoNormal"><a title="So, who is Peter Austen?" href="{CCM:CID_322}"><strong>So, who is Peter Austen?</strong></a></h3>\r\n<p><img style="float: left; margin-right: 20px;" src="{CCM:FID_71}" alt="Peter_pic2.jpg" width="94" height="111" /></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Hospitality Entrepreneur (HE) was founded in July 2013 by Peter Austen. Peter is MD of the hospitality operations consultants Innventive, having spent the last 20 years immersed in hospitality business<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"> </span>coaching and operating pubs, restaurants, bars and hotels himself.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><a title="So, who is Peter Austen?" href="{CCM:CID_322}"><strong>Find out more</strong></a></p>\r\n<p></p>'),
(821, '<h1>We Don''t Just Waffle About Hospitality Entrepreneurship...</h1>\r\n<div class="under-big-title"><br />\r\n<p>We approach hospitality from a unique perspective. We all know that the challenges and demands of owning and running a restaurant, pub, bar, caf or hotel can be extreme, so extreme that the business usually ends up controlling you, preventing you from realising your goals and ambitions. So, since the 1990''s and even more since 2001 we''ve been travelling the ''new'' world of hospitality, learning it, practising it and teaching it like no one else.</p>\r\n<p>The result is <strong>Hospitality Entrepreneur (HE)</strong> a new ''Go to'' information and advice website, a members'' ''Club'' and above all a ''get down and dirty'' practical service for smart hospitality business owners. No bland corporate waffle here, created just to fill up a company webpage. Instead, <em>valuable</em> information, success secrets from those at the top of the hospitality tree and exclusive access to services and systems that we consider to be the best way to grow a solid business.</p>\r\n<strong>Our mission will never change. We ensure that you get:</strong></div>\r\n<div class="under-big-title">\r\n<ul class="list-better">\r\n<li>Better <strong>profits</strong></li>\r\n<li>Better <strong>knowledge</strong></li>\r\n<li>Better <strong>peace of mind</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<h3>How do we do this?</h3>\r\n<p>Founder Peter Austen has been in the business of performance coaching for hundreds of hospitality businesses since 1993, before anyone used that term. We hate to boast, but today we are a collaboration of leading industry professionals and companies, with thousands of happy clients and unrivalled expertise in building and running successful hospitality businesses.</p>\r\n<br />Every month we will release the best and latest industry advice (see Resources) to our members. This will be available for your use as and when you want it, 24/7, ready for you and your staff to implement straight away in your business. <br /><br />In addition to the best business advice, our members also enjoy privileged access to our Partner business services. <br /><br /><strong><em> Do you want to expand your business but dont know how?</em> </strong><br /><br /><strong><em> Would you like to radically increase your businesss profits whilst decreasing its reliance on YOU?</em> </strong><br /><br /><strong><em> Does your business control you, rather than the other way around?</em></strong> <br /><br />If the answer to any of these questions is ''YES'', then you are a hospitality entrepreneur, so join our Club today.</div>\r\n<h5></h5>'),
(822, '<div class="member-benefit">\r\n<h4>Join Today</h4>\r\n<p>Join today, either by taking advantage of our Starter membership 30 day <strong>FREE</strong> trial or, if you''ve been lucky enough to have been contacted by one of our Partner businesses, using your exclusive VIP Launch Offer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Starter membership - 30 day FREE trial</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dip your toe in, receive a FREE copy of the 245 page ''Botty''s Rules'', enjoy access to 70% of the HE website and resources, as well as privileged access to our Partner business services<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Exclusive VIP Launch Offer</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong>Our VIP Launch Offer, including 3 months extra subscription for <strong>FREE, </strong>is available to friends of our Partner businesses, those who complete our <a href="http://hospitalityentrepreneur.com/survey.html">2 minute survey</a> and those who take out annual subscription</p>\r\n<p>Either way, join the HE Club now and start to:</p>\r\n Attract and KEEP more customers<br /> Increase your bottom line profits<br /> Access exclusive member business resources 24/7<br /> Access easy-to-implement business growth secrets<br /> Benefit from the latest purchasing, marketing, training, food costing and operations support<br /> Start implementing and benefitting, or your money back\r\n<p>It''s all here for as little as 10 (plus VAT) per month</p>\r\n</div>'),
(823, '<h4>Articles, blogs, checklists and numerous trade secrets</h4>\r\n<p><img src="http://hospitalityentrepreneur.com/member/images/about-partners/partners-pics.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p>Clockwise from top left: <strong>Andrew Pring, Carol Emmas, Peter Austen, Nigel Botterill and Ali Carter<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>A sprinkling of the hottest advice and help is provided by our assortment of writers and business experts.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Andrew Pring</strong>, our Business Editor has plenty to say on the business issues that are constantly changing the hospitality sector. With experience as editor at the Licensee &amp; Morning Advertiser and BII Business, he knows a fair bit about the pub industry especially. Also, <strong>Carol Emmas </strong>joins us from a recent stint as taste editor at Harpers Wine &amp; Spirit trade review when shes not writing for numerous hospitality publications.</p>\r\n<p>Insight and inspiration is provided by one of the countrys best known serial entrepreneurs, <strong>Nigel Botterill</strong>. He knows a fair bit about starting, expanding and selling multi-million pound businesses, having done that himself from scratch eight (at the last count!) times in the last ten years.</p>\r\n<p>Practical operational advice, including checklists, templates and behind the scenes insights, is also provided by <strong>Peter Austen</strong> and <strong>Ali Carter</strong>, who have all the war stories and overview necessary after owning and running a variety of super-successful restaurants, hotels, pubs and bars themselves.</p>'),
