(1229, '<p>The world seems to be going mad for quotations, especially those that motivate us, as most of our Facebook friends timeline posts will show us. Like quotations or not, theyre rarely invented and usually act as a great reminder of how super-successful people have achieved all sorts of goals in the past. Ali Carter brought this quote to my attention yesterday:</p>\r\n<p>What is the distance between someone who achieves their goals consistently and those who spend their lives and careers merely following? The extra mile (US business guru Gary Blair)</p>\r\n<p>OK, so I dont know Gary Blair. However, every staff appraisal Ive ever conducted and self appraisal form Ive ever issued asksthe staff member to consider whether or not they go the extra mile and how often?</p>\r\n<p>A few thoughts. Have you explained clearly what is expected of them and discussed each others definition of this elusive extra mile? Have you recognised them for going the extra bit and thanked them for it? You can bet they wont do it again if you dont, so why not go the extra mile yourself and really look for good actions and examples of your staff team members going the extra mile? Its One small step for man, but a huge potential step for hospitality business kind, or whatever Neil Armstrong said.</p>'),
