(581, 73, 275, 'Bond Dickson', 'Marvellous PR', 'Marvellous PR from Lucy Matthews  The UK Entrepreneurs PR Expert', 'In a 30+ year career as a PR consultant, Lucy Matthews has worked with a huge range of clients in B2B and B2C markets, around the world, from industrial floor cleaning manufacturers, to football clubs; property developers to therapists; Pepsi to pasta ready meals; photographers to authors; big businesses to entrepreneurs and small start-ups; helping them to build their profile and get free editorial.\r\n\r\nArmed with this experience, Lucy created Marvellous PR, which is not your average generic marketing, advertising or PR agency; it is a pure PR resource, providing HE members with all the tools you need to get your reputation built.  Either by letting Lucy do it all for you, or by learning, with her help and guidance, how to do it for yourselves, which is where the Marvellous ''PR Toolkit'' comes in, with an exclusive deal for HE members.\r\n', 275, 'Say hello'),
(583, 74, 275, 'Bond Dickson', 'Bramble Buzz', 'Social Media expertise from Julia Bramble  The UK Entrepreneurs Social Media Expert', 'Julia has a sound conviction that through social media, hospitality businesses have access to hundreds of thousands of people, all of whom might be interested, in some way, in your business. She helps you channel that power, so that you can do it right and get the results you want and need for your business. She fervently believes that every single business owner should be using social media  that they should not be intimidated by it, or be put off by horror stories about how long it all takes. She''s part of HE to quash those fears and make it all accessible and successful for you.\r\n\r\nIn her role as social media guru and preferred supplier to the Entrepreneur''s Circle, she''s used to working 1:1, or with a small group at most, on one social network at a time, ensuring that you understand the power each network has to transform your business, to a plan which she insists all HE members put in place. \r\n\r\nThe social media help and advice Julia offers is rooted in very sound, up-to-the-minute thinking in terms of marketing, customer service, planning for business goals, selling . but  most importantly  as this is the most important task for any business owner . getting and keeping customers. No customers  no business!', 275, 'Say hello'),
