(366, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '<script type="text/javascript">var switchTo5x=true;</script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript" src="http://w.sharethis.com/button/buttons.js"></script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript">stLight.options({publisher: "e2a1e254-6129-47e5-91da-4a115c949cc8", doNotHash: false, doNotCopy: false, hashAddressBar: false});</script>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, '<p><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/oCrnIpRicPc?&amp;rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;autohide=1" frameborder="0" width="420" height="315"></iframe></p>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(310, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '<script type="text/javascript">var switchTo5x=true;</script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript" src="http://w.sharethis.com/button/buttons.js"></script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript">stLight.options({publisher: "e2a1e254-6129-47e5-91da-4a115c949cc8", doNotHash: false, doNotCopy: false, hashAddressBar: false});</script>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, '<div>Lately there seems to be just too much choice in life and it''s tiring. For instance, only a few years ago we had five TV stations, now there are hundreds and it takes forever to pick a channel if youre just lazily scrolling through via remote control. Then take social media; if you want to keep up with goings on there is Twitter, Facebook, Pintrest and blogs galore. We could lose days of our lives on Twitter alone choosing what links we want to click on to. If you totted up all the minutes spent making across-the-board choices, I reckon wed lose months of our lives.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Wine choice is the same. Sometimes when youre staring at the shelves the bottles just swim into one. I walked out of M&amp;S today empty handed, because frankly I just couldnt be bothered to make a decision in this sweltering heat. It was one decision too many after having to select a pair of glasses from a hundred frames and choosing what I was going to have for supper from the shelves of chicken variations. Of course Im not really grumbling (and Id be certainly grumbling if the choice was taken away) but occasionally I like not to have to think. I was most impressed when I spoke to a New York bar owner last year on the <a href="http://www.winesofgermany.co.uk/events/upcoming-events-31-days-of-german-riesling">31 Days of Riesling</a>trip to Germany who said for a month in his bar if customers wanted a white wine by the glass their only option was Riesling; the only decision they had to make was the country of origin and style. He said people loved being told what to do and as a result his like-by-like, by-the-glass sales shot up.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>I was recently in the Rhne Valley visiting <a href="http://www.vintur.fr/en/about.htm">Domaine Vintur</a> which is owned by Englishman Graham Shore and overseen by his innovative Yorkshire born wine maker, James Wood. You know, its so nice, just to have a simple selection of good wines, I mused, staring at its concise, non fussy and clearly packaged range. Ive been on many a wine trip and when youre faced with a sea of bottles to taste from a single producer it can be very off-putting.<br /> <br /> <br />\r\n<div class="separator"></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>So, in the theme of things Ill keep it simple: The Domaine Vintur Cuve Le Gentleman 2011 (rrp 14.80), is aromatic and beautifully elegant. The Domaine Vintur White Tradition, Grenache Blanc, 2012 (rrp 10.56), really grew on me through the days visit and has obviously grown on others too, having won the Trophe Concours du Ventoux 2013 for the best white in the whole appellation. Plus the Domaine Vintur Ros 2012, Vin de Pays de la Mediterrane (9.71) was dry, clean and drinking perfectly on that beautiful French summers day.<strong>bibendum</strong>-wine.co.uk</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<p><br /> And with that in mind, ifI was eating out today Id go to <a href="http://relaisdevenise.com/">Le Relais de Venise</a> because there is no menu, which is not taxing to the brain at all. You just tell the waitress how you like your steak and then back it comes with salad and chips. Sometimes there''s a lot to be said about just keeping it simple.<br /> </p>\r\n<div class="separator"></div>\r\n<div></div>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(327, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '<script type="text/javascript">var switchTo5x=true;</script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript" src="http://w.sharethis.com/button/buttons.js"></script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript">stLight.options({publisher: "e2a1e254-6129-47e5-91da-4a115c949cc8", doNotHash: false, doNotCopy: false, hashAddressBar: false});</script>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Never think you can survive on word-of-mouth publicity  everything you do should be done with an eye on attracting more people into your restaurant.</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />Guests are the lifeblood of your business and you need to understand their value to you before you work out how much to spend on attracting new diners. If you dont know what the value of a customer is to your business, then you need to.</p>\r\n<p><br />In the restaurant industry, you need to consider that some guests will only dine with you once, if they are passing through the town, say, or visiting friends. The money you spend advertising to these prospects is less important than the money you spend on your other regular guests or guest with potential to come back. The lifetime value of regular diners at your restaurant is huge. If you can<br />convince people to return to your restaurant every week for years, your investment in marketing can be much higher because of the immense value such guests bring to your business.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Continues..</strong></h4>\r\n<p>DOWNLOAD PDF TO READ MORE:</p>\r\n<p><a href="/download_file/view/113/">7_Golden_Rules.pdf</a></p>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
