(315, '\r\n Share This \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  Licensing Checklist, by Ewen Macgregor, Bond Dickinson LLP  Check list for LicenseesIt is advisable for licence holders to keep a file of all relevant licensing information so that this can be accessed quickly and, where required, displayed in the appropriate part of the premises:  Copy of your licence summary on display in the premises  A copy of your licence, summary and current approved layout plan available for inspection  Copies of any other permission  e.g. Gambling Act 2005 licence, marriage licence, gaming machine permit, tables and chairs licence/planning permission  on display where required and/or available for inspection  No Smoking signage displayed  Notice under s.57 of the Licensing Act 2003 confirming who has custody of the licence on display [England only] Copies of personal licences for all those employed at the premises  Authorisation for sales of alcohol  Staff training records  Refusals Log  Incident Log  Door security sign in/sign out log book  Up to date Fire Risk Assessment  Up to date General and Specific Risk Assessments  Contact details for the Local Authority Licensing Officer  Contact details for the Local Police Licensing Officer  Contact details for Gambling Commission Compliance manager (where applicable)  Check list of who to contact within your organisation in the event of an incident Scotland Only Statutory training records for all members of staff involved in the sale or service of alcohol  Statutory Notice displayed in relation to the sale of alcohol to those under the age of 18  Statutory notice as to whether or not those under the age of 18 are permitted access to the premises  Contact details for the local Licensing Standards Officer www.bonddickinson.comBD.259This communication is provided for general information only and does not constitute legal or other professional advice. You should consult a suitably qualified lawyer on any specific legal problem or matter.\r\n\r\n\r\